    {
        "content": "<p>What would be the best spelling of the statement \"<code>a</code> is the unique <code>α</code> such that <code>p a</code>\"? I saw <code>∃! a : α, p a</code>, but it doesn't say anything about which <code>a</code> this is. It can also be directly expanded as <code>p a ∧ ∀ b : α, p b → b = a</code>, but that requires duplicating <code>a</code> and <code>p</code> which I don't really like.</p>",
        "id": 437588515,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1715150985
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could use <code>{x | p x} = {a}</code></p>",
        "id": 437601167,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1715156279
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though <code>p b ↔ b = a</code> is probably more useful</p>",
        "id": 437601352,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1715156341
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.60a.60.20is.20the.20unique.20.60.CE.B1.60.20such.20that.20.60p.20a.60/near/437601352\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Though <code>p b ↔ b = a</code> is probably more useful</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This seems great, thanks!</p>",
